<HL>
   AirTran's Mesaba Unit Traffic
</HL>
<DATE>
06/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A12
</SO>
<CO>
   ATCC
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   MINNEAPOLIS -- Mesaba Aviation Inc., a unit of AirTran
Corp., said its May traffic rose 19% to 15.4 million revenue
passenger miles from 12.9 million a year earlier.
   A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger flown one
mile.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The carrier, which operates as Northwest Airlink, said its
load factor, or percentage of available seats filled, fell to
48% from 52.4%.
</TEXT>
