<HL>
   Hong Kong Exports Decline
</HL>
<DATE>
06/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- The value of Hong Kong's exports of locally
made goods fell 3% in the first quarter and 1% in March from
a year earlier, government figures show.
   Hong Kong import values rose 2% in the quarter and 6% in
March.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Among re-exported items, the British colony's shipments of
raw materials and semi-manufactured goods were down 5% in the
quarter and 2% in the month, while re-exports of foodstuffs
dropped 11% in the quarter and 13% in March. Re-exports of
fuels, however, soared 175% during the month and 89% in the
quarter, while those of consumer goods jumped 28% in the
quarter and 36% in March.
