<HL>
   Porsche Unit Recalls Cars
</HL>
<DATE>
06/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<CO>
   G.POR
</CO>
<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   RENO, Nev. -- The U.S. sales arm of Porsche AG said it is
recalling 19 of its 928 S4 and 928 GT models because of a
defect that could cause fuel leaks and, potentially, fires.
   Porsche said the fuel tanks of the affected models are
attached to the car with a mounting nut that could crack. As
a result, fuel could leak from the tank. If the gasoline
comes in contact with a hot exhaust system, a fire might
occur. The auto maker said it isn't aware of any fires,
accidents or injuries caused by the defect.
</LP>
<TEXT>
