<HL>
   Norway's Consumer Prices Rise
</HL>
<DATE>
06/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   OSLO -- Norway's consumer prices rose 0.2% for the month
ending May 15 and were up 3.9% from the year-earlier period,
the state Central Bureau of Statistics said.
   Travel and transportation showed the sharpest increase,
with that May index up 1.1% from April and 2.1% from May
1989, the bureau said. Food prices declined 0.1% in May from
April.
</LP>
