<LP>
   CF INCOME PARTNERS LIMITED PARTNERSHIP (Los Angeles) --
Jeffrey H. Lynford, 42 years old, was elected vice chairman
and chief financial officer of CF Management Corp., the
general partner of CF Income. As chief financial officer, he
succeeds Raymond H. Olinger, 61, who retires July 1. The post
of vice chairman is newly created. Mr. Lynford is chairman of
Wellsford Group Inc., an affiliate of Wellsford Capital
Partners Limited Partnership, which acquired 20% of CF
Management late last year. CF Partners invests in
income-producing multifamily residential, commercial and
industrial properties.
