   Third-Quarter Net Income
   Declined on Special Items
</HL>
<DATE>
06/12/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16
</SO>
<CO>
   ETCO
</CO>
<LP>
   Earth Technology Corp. said net income for the third
quarter ended May 25 was reduced about $100,000, or three
cents a share, because of non-operating items.
   The items include a percentage of a restated operating
loss at Waste Processor Industries Inc., in which Earth
Technology holds a 24% stake, and a valuation adjustment from
a deferred compensation arrangement in Earth Technology's
acquisition of Alternative Ways Inc.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   A year earlier, the Long Beach, Calif., company had profit
of $32,952, or one cent a share, on revenue of $6 million.
The consulting firm, specializing in environmental and
engineering issues, said it will release full results in
about 10 days.
